        "content": "<p>Announcing Software Should Work, an independent conference on software reliability on July 16-17 in Columbia, MO.</p>\n<p>Software is usually buggy and slow, but it doesn't have to be. That's why I’m organizing a conference on the tools and techniques we use to make it correct and fast instead. </p>\n<p>If you're excited about Roc, there's a very good chance you'll enjoy this conference too.<br>\n<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"281383\">@Richard Feldman</span>, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"726142\">@Ray Myers</span>, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"666594\">@John Murray</span>,  <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"406911\">@Andrew Kelley</span> , and Hillel Wayne are all speaking. I'd love to have a strong contingent of Roc fans at SSW and really we already do. <span aria-label=\"smiley\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f603\" role=\"img\" title=\"smiley\">:smiley:</span> </p>\n<p>A huge thank you to RWX (<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"498818\">@Dan Manges</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"465225\">@Tommy Graves</span>) and our other sponsors for helping make the conference possible.</p>\n<p>Tickets are available now <a href=\"https://softwareshould.work\">https://softwareshould.work</a><br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/7dEcHXGzvFSDz4a8u18ZYjcW/ssw_overview.png\">ssw_overview.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/7dEcHXGzvFSDz4a8u18ZYjcW/ssw_overview.png\" title=\"ssw_overview.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1780x1260\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/22008/7dEcHXGzvFSDz4a8u18ZYjcW/ssw_overview.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
